summary: Comprehensive testing of Ocean Super App completed after adding demo data and new services (experiences, on-demand services, subscriptions, notifications). Backend APIs are 100% functional with all endpoints working correctly. Frontend pages load and function properly but lack main navigation links for service discovery.

design_issues.issue: No navigation links to new services (food, rides, hotels, experiences, services, subscriptions) in main header navigation
design_issues.impact: Users cannot discover new services easily - they must know direct URLs

passed_tests: Backend API: GET /api/experiences/types - Returns 5 experience types
Backend API: GET /api/experiences/ - Returns 5 experiences with demo data
Backend API: GET /api/services/types - Returns 8 service types
Backend API: GET /api/services/ - Returns 6 on-demand services
Backend API: GET /api/subscriptions/plans - Returns 3 subscription plans
Backend API: All authenticated endpoints working correctly
Frontend: All service pages load correctly via direct URLs
Frontend: Experiences page displays 5 experience types and cards
Frontend: Services page displays 6 service cards with booking functionality
Frontend: Subscriptions page displays 3 plans with billing cycle toggle
Frontend: Service filtering and booking modals work correctly
Frontend: Arabic localization working properly across all pages
Backend: Login with admin credentials successful
Backend: All CRUD operations for new services working
Backend: Demo data properly seeded (8 restaurants, 8 hotels, 5 experiences, 6 services, 3 subscriptions)
action_item_for_main_agent: Add navigation links to new services in main header navigation. Users currently cannot discover the new services (food, rides, hotels, experiences, services, subscriptions) from the main navigation menu. All services are fully functional but not accessible through normal user flow.
